        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 31 at 4:56PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 456 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was near Cave Spring, or 7 miles
north of Cedartown, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Rome, Cedartown, Aragon, Cave Spring, Seney, and Lindale.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
